> This is just the beginning. Next year, you'll be left with the grandfather
> to look after together.

The national police also weighed in on the debate.

> ¡Siempre hay una alternativa al abandono animal! Un vecino caritativo… o
> toda la comunidad🙃.  
>  Besines para [#PESESIN](https://twitter.com/hashtag/PESESIN?src=hash) 🐟
>
> 💙 [#animals](https://twitter.com/hashtag/animals?src=hash)
> <https://t.co/xLrwq6b80d>
>
> — Policía Nacional (@policia) [11 de julio de
> 2017](https://twitter.com/policia/status/884900990025158657)

> There's always an alternative to abandoning an animal! A caring neighbour…
> or the whole community🙃. Neighbours for
> [#PESESIN](https://twitter.com/hashtag/PESESIN?src=hash) 🐟

Pesesín himself, who has a Twitter account, gave his opinion on his unexpected
rise to fame:

> Splash.
>
> — Pesesín (@SoyPesesin) [July 12
> 2017](https://twitter.com/SoyPesesin/status/885245360544919553)

At the end of the week, we met Yurena, Pesesín's owner. Stunned by the fame
that her pet had garnered, she explained her side of the story during an
[interview with the Spanish TV channel Cuatro
TV](http://www.cuatro.com/cronicacuatro/Pesesin-pez-momento-visitamos-
hogar_2_2401905180.html), in which she said that a trip came up with her
parents, but she couldn't take the fish with her. After asking friends and
acquaintances [to take care of him] without any success, she decided to leave
him in the hands of fate…and the solidarity of her neighbours.

After seeing Pesesín looking well, Yurena felt immense gratitude towards her
neighbours and wanted to express her thanks by leaving another note in the
same spot that goldfish bowl had been during her trip:

[![Nota de agradecimiento de Pesesín a los
vecinos](https://es.globalvoices.org/wp-
content/uploads/2017/07/pesesin2.jpg)](https://twitter.com/Yureninalove/status/885074429335785472?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&ref_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gonzoo.com%2Factualidad%2Fstory%2Fla-
duena-del-pez-celebrity-ya-esta-en-casa-y-cuando-volvi-pesesin-era-
famoso-5871%2F)

A thank you note from Pesesín to the neighbours that had looked after him so
well. Image shared by Yurena Sabio on Twitter.

> MANY THANKS TO ALL THE NEIGHBOURS!
>
> On behalf of Pesesín and with special mention to those who changed the water
> and bought food. Although the food that was left was meant to last a few
> months and now I need to put him on a diet for a few days, he has loved
> getting to know you.

On Pesesín's story's thread, a Twitter user took advantage of the good nature
that the police usually show on the microblogging site, making this
suggestion:

> ¡Hola,[@policia](https://twitter.com/policia)!
>
> Me gustaría que la próxima trama policial que tengáis la llamaseis
> «Pesesín».[#elcasoPesesín](https://twitter.com/hashtag/elcasoPeses%C3%ADn?src=hash)

> Hello, [@](https://twitter.com/policia)police! I would like you to call the
> next police investigation you have,
> “Pesesín”.[#Pesesín](https://twitter.com/hashtag/elcasoPeses%C3%ADn?src=hash)case

To which the popular account replied:

> 🤔🤔🤔… ¡¡Trato hecho!! Prometemos la operación “Pesesín” cuando pesquemos🚔 un
> pez gordo!! <https://t.co/hsuI9rvib2>
>
> — Policía Nacional (@policia) [July 13
> 2017](https://twitter.com/policia/status/885498425860665344)

> 🤔🤔🤔…Done deal! We promise to call the operation ‘Pesesín’ when we catch a
> big fish [a big criminal]!

